discs with outer edges and\nSB falling as r**-3.5. Systems with sharper outer edges, barring other\nconfining agents, could still be explained by ``natural'' collisional evolution\nif their dynamical excitation is very low. We show that such a dynamically-cold\ncase provides a satisfactory fit for HR4796A\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 24 Jan 2008 10:00:08 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 28 Jan 2008 10:14:53 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 4 Feb 2008 10:41:03 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-13"}
